SESSIONS
--------
- start anonymous session
    
    $ tmux

- get help

    <pfx> ?
    
- start anonymous session
        
        $ tmux

- start named sessions

    $ tmux new-session -s basic
    
    or

    $ tmux new -s basic

- detaching session

    <pfx> d

- listing sessions
    
    $ tmux list-sessions
    $ tmux ls

- create a session in the background

    $ tmux new -s bg_session -d

- attaching to session

    $ tmux attach
    $ tmux attach -t bg_session

- killing session
    
    $ tmux kill-session -t bg_session

- create a new session and name the first window
    
    $ tmux new -s windows -n shell

- entering command mode

    <pfx> :


WINDOWS
-------
- create a new window

    <pfx> c

- create a new window

    :new-window -n console

- start a new window and launch a program

    :new-window -n processes "top"


- renaming a window
    
    <pfx> ,

- listing windows

    <pfx> w
    <pfx> f <enter>

- moving between windows
    
    # next
    <pfx> n 
    
    # previous
    <pfx> p

    # last window
    <pfx> ctrl-a

    # using window index
    <pfx> 0
    <pfx> 1
    <pfx> 5

    # using window's name
    <pfx> f + [first few characters of window's name]

- closing window

    <pfx> &

- dividing a window vertically

    <pfx> %

- dividing a window horizontally

    <pfx> "

- momentarily display pane number in each pane

    <pfx> q
    
- moving between panes    

    <pfx> o
    <pfx> left|right|up|down

- cycling through pane layouts
    
    <pfx> <space>

- closing a pane
    
    <pfx> x

- checking version

    $ tmux -V

